===Etymology===
From French ''[[bouteille]]''

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈbɒt(ə)l/}} (''UK'') ''or'' {{IPA|/ˈbɑt(ə)l/}} (''US'') ''or'' {{IPA|/ˈbɑɾ(ə)l/}} (''CA'')
*{{SAMPA|/"bQt(@)l/}} (''UK'') ''or'' {{SAMPA|/"bAt(@)l/}} (''US'')
*{{audio|en-us-bottle.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*{{audio|en-ca-bottle.ogg|Audio (CA)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒtəl|-ɒtəl]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A container, typically made of glass and having a tapered neck, used for holding liquids.
#: ''Beer is often sold in '''bottles'''.''
# The contents of such a container.
#: ''I only drank a '''bottle''' of beer.''
# A container with a rubber nipple used for giving liquids to infants, in full : baby's bottle, feeding bottle, nursing bottle {{US}}.
#: ''The baby wants a '''bottle'''.''
# {{UK}} [[Nerve]], [[courage]].
#: ''You don't have the '''bottle''' to do that!''
#: ''He was going to ask her out, but he lost his '''bottle''' when he saw her.''

